## 🔍 Detection

| Detection | AWS Service | Event |
|---|---|---|
| Metadata API abuse | CloudTrail | `GetCredentials` from unusual source |
| Credentials used from unexpected IP | CloudTrail | AssumeRole from external IP |
| Unusual S3 access | CloudTrail | `ListBuckets` + `GetObject` by WAF role |
| SSRF attempt | WAF / VPC Flow Logs | Outbound traffic to 169.254.169.254 |
| Mass S3 enumeration | GuardDuty | Finding: `Discovery:S3/MaliciousIPCaller` |

**Key CloudTrail Events to Alert On:**
```
EventName = GetObject AND UserAgent != expected-application
EventName = ListBuckets AND SourceIPAddress != known-range
```

---

## 🛡️ Remediation

| Misconfiguration | Fix |
|---|---|
| IMDSv1 enabled | Enforce **IMDSv2** on all EC2 instances — requires session token, blocks SSRF |
| Proxy forwards to metadata IP | Block outbound requests to `169.254.169.254` at proxy/WAF level |
| WAF role has S3 access | Apply least privilege — WAF roles should never access cardholder data |
| No S3 bucket policy | Restrict S3 access to specific roles/IPs only |
| No GuardDuty | Enable GuardDuty for automated threat detection |

**Enforce IMDSv2 (most important fix):**
```bash
aws ec2 modify-instance-metadata-options \
  --instance-id <instance-id> \
  --http-tokens required \
  --http-endpoint enabled
```

