## 📰 Real World Reference

This attack mirrors the **Capital One Data Breach (2019)**:
- Attacker exploited a misconfigured WAF on EC2
- Used SSRF to reach the metadata service
- Stole IAM role credentials
- Accessed S3 buckets containing 100+ million customer records
- Result: $80 million fine, massive reputational damage
